The article discusses the funding announcement to expand Certified Community Behavioral Health Clinics (CCBHCs), which aim to provide evidence-based mental health services to individuals regardless of their ability to pay. The clinics operate 24/7 and offer mental health and substance use care. This funding is part of the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act, the American Rescue Plan, and this year's budget. The article also highlights the importance of addressing the mental health crisis and mentions previous efforts, such as signing the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act and providing resources for school-based mental health professionals and trauma-informed services. The administration plans to announce further resources to support mental health workers and strengthen mental health services in the coming weeks. The overall goal is to ensure that everyone has access to mental health services and support when needed.